relation.text: March 1797 Mrs Dickenson & her husband had their portraits taken
tomorrow Morng at 11 -- he also went
saw Miſs Stevens ( who is now
Friday -- Schram to Mr. Dickenson -- Mr. D . L & I. went
saw her & ye . 2 Lady Montgommerys ye . eldest 11 ye . 6 th of next Mont ( Lady Mary ) the youngest Ly . Susan 14 Months
tomorrow at 10-6 Pr . Week -- much amused wth . his volubility -- of tongue -- went
sent her home -- shew 'd Louisa & c her Drawg- Book Sunday
Wednesday -- Miſs H : More Mrs. Bouvries & I din
s daughter there -- an agreeable young Woman 26 years
came from Windsor to day on busineſs -- Monday
did not get home till past 12 . Tuesday
work 'd in his Garden a few months ago
had shewn her Mother & Sisters some years
tomorrow look 'd much than when I saw
a few days . Made visits to Mrs. Garrick ( saw
came home -- Letter Mrs. Pepys -- & c -- Saturday
saw -- her 3 boys & girls -- Eldest Mrs. Glover 10 last Novbr youngest boy 1 Year
had made a great Fortune in India -- he is ten Years
s -- Miſs A Clarke in the Morng -- Tuesday March 7
put her to bed at 7 -- Thursday
March 1797 Mrs. Hunter to Mrs Campbell who I thank
a visit -- who was at least 30 Years
represented -- one of his Brothers was in England some years
tomorrow & c Ly- Herries to Mrs. Turton & c he went out
— for ¼ hour Ly C— had been to Ly- Wake -- Mr- D— & Mrs. Carter Sunday 12 March
Thursday Afternoon -- Recd- Rundells frm . Dery . sat
s cold better -- Meſsages Dr . Mrs. Delany & c Monday
married to Mrs Hunter to day Wednesday
March 1797 Campel & Ly A Gammon to Mrs- Porteus Miſs Holyor'yd & c : in ye . Morng -- he talk
came in after dinner -- Cudg l e l playing & c & c -- ye . 5 daughter -- Lord Warwick 15 -- there are 6 -- Charles ye Youngest at Warwick Castle aged 6 months
delighted with Miſs Fox who is 3 Years
found them at tea -- Robert readg ye newspaper to the once much talk 'd of Louisa who is now
March 1797 / Lord Cremorne -- Lord C . to Col Barré & she went
look 'd ill & had this bad Cold Friday
March 1797 Corporal Lyle to Lord Warwick s
found her Opera Box Servts- every thing next year
18 March 1797 Ly- Herries to Mr D -- Invitations to Mr. Heavyside -- Louisa & c -- Miranda Johnstone & Orme came
told me Langton had 3 boys -- Algernon Langton is now
tomorrow Eveg- We did not home till past 11 -- I took
met there Mr. D -- the Montagus & c -- 20 th - Monday
March 1797 -- Mrs. Carter Ly- Ch— Wentworth Mrs- Townsend & her Cousin & c . Ly Louisa Clayton went
staid with us till 12 o'Clock -- Wednesday

seems Modest good temper 'd -- Sat ¼ of an Hour wth- Mrs. H Browne -- talk of young Ly Cicilia Johnstone youngest Ly Mary Coke that was -- she has been 16 times wth . Child in abt 12 or 13 or 14 Years
lost her Eldest Girl -- who was an idiot at 13 Years
Yesterday Mrs . Fielding -- Mr D— to Ld Cremorne -- 2 young Langtons call
came home -- Sr Chs Blagdon call 'd this Morng Alderman Harley & c Friday
March 1797 -- Dr Douglaſs to Miſs Elliot wrote
Saturday 25 th Mrs- Pepys -- Ly Clermont to Mr : Mat : Montagu -- Mr : Langton call 'd & c -- Mr Cambridge Schram & I went
staid wth . her till 11 oClock -- Sunday
invited me to her House on Wednesday
March 1797 -- Paid Lady Prescot 12 leſsons 1-11-6 Sr Lucas 's
took Lady H home she was very indifferent Miſs Bloſset call 'd Thursday
s -- Mrs Margaret Tryon ( née Wake ) & Lady Clayton -- Sr : -- + Miſs Tryon Miss ( Margaret ) Tryon Ly Frances Fitzwilliam . & c Thursday
March 1797 Lord FitzwilliamMarquis Rockingham ) Mrs. Wedell to Ly -- she went
March 1797 Sent Note to Mr Baker -- Ly Mary Coke to Ly- Fitzwilliam & she & Papa went
talk 'd of Noverre & c the little boy 5 -- the Girl 3 in May
ye . sad accident Genl . Clinton had 2 Years ago
came home ¼ past 11 oClock Mr. Heaviside & c : had call 'd in ye Morng -- Saturday
April 1797 -- Miſs Bloſset Mr to Mrs. de Salis -- she sent
April 1797 -- Snow -- Counteſs Dowg Rothes came
